# Supabase Postgres pooling

ADR-003. Two URLs. Don't mix them up.

## Two URLs, two purposes

| Var                   | Port | Mode                  | Used by                       |
| --------------------- | ---- | --------------------- | ----------------------------- |
| `DATABASE_URL`        | 6543 | PgBouncer transaction | App runtime (all queries)     |
| `DATABASE_URL_DIRECT` | 5432 | Direct session        | `drizzle-kit` migrations ONLY |

## App client — `prepare: false` is MANDATORY

```ts
// src/db/client.ts
import { drizzle } from "drizzle-orm/postgres-js";
import postgres from "postgres";
import * as schema from "./schema";
import * as relations from "./schema/_relations";
import { env } from "@/lib/env";

const sql = postgres(env.DATABASE_URL, {
  prepare: false, // ← REQUIRED. PgBouncer in transaction mode
  //   doesn't preserve prepared statements
  //   across queries. Without this, you get:
  //   "prepared statement s1 already exists"
  //   under load. Random, hard to reproduce.
  max: 10, // small pool; the pool we actually use is PgBouncer's
  idle_timeout: 30,
});

export const db = drizzle(sql, {
  schema: { ...schema, ...relations },
  logger: env.NODE_ENV === "development",
});
```

## `drizzle-kit` — uses the DIRECT URL

```ts
// drizzle.config.ts
import type { Config } from "drizzle-kit";
import { env } from "@/lib/env";

export default {
  schema: "./src/db/schema/*.ts",
  out: "./drizzle",
  dialect: "postgresql",
  dbCredentials: {
    url: env.DATABASE_URL_DIRECT, // direct, NOT pooled
  },
  verbose: true,
  strict: true,
} satisfies Config;
```

If you run `pnpm db:migrate` and see `CREATE TYPE` errors or `CONCURRENTLY` syntax errors, you're going through the pooler. Check the URL.

## NEVER instantiate a second client

```ts
// ❌ Don't do this in /lib/something/db.ts
import postgres from "postgres";

const sql = postgres(env.DATABASE_URL); // forgot prepare: false
// → random failures under load
```

All queries go through the single `db` export from `@/db/client`.

## Migration in CI / production

CI does NOT run migrations. Production migrations are manual:

```bash
DATABASE_URL_DIRECT="<prod direct>" pnpm db:migrate
```

See `RUNBOOK §3.6` for full procedure.

